# Quantitative Aptitude – Set 1 (Top Cognitive Questions)

## **1. Percentage**

A number increases from 480 to 600. What is the percentage increase?

## **2. Profit & Loss**

An item is bought for ₹750 and sold for ₹900. Find the profit percentage.

## **3. Time & Work**

A can complete a work in 15 days, B can complete the same work in 20 days. How long will they take together?

## **4. Ratio & Proportion**

The ratio of the ages of A and B is 7:5. If their total age is 48, find their ages.

## **5. Simple Interest**

Calculate SI on ₹12,000 at 6% per annum for 2 years.

## **6. Speed, Distance & Time**

A man walks at 6 km/h. How long will he take to cover 24 km?

## **7. Averages**

The average of 5 numbers is 18. If one number (24) is removed, what is the new average?

## **8. Number System**

How many even numbers are there between 300 and 400?

## **9. Simplification**

Solve: (36 ÷ 6) × (15 − 9) + 27

## **10. Mixture & Alligation**

A mixture contains 30 liters of milk and 10 liters of water. How much milk should be added to make the ratio 5:1?
